<br>
Lord of the Rings, if you have not read this you can come shoot me in my mangina...  <br>
<br>
The Robot series/Foundation series, This is a HUGE amount of books, The Foundations is very good, and it ties into the robot series at the end.  Also the Foundation was awarded the &quot;Best Sci Fi trilogy ever&quot; a number of years ago, before a lot of awards like this came out.  &quot;I Robot&quot; is the start of the Robot series, and there are like 8 or so in it, and about 5 in the Foundation.  Isaac Asimov is very good and you will see a lot of stuff that is in may series/books these days in there.<br>
<br>
Dune, the first book is by far the best, but if you like political and social &quot;I fucked you harder&quot; settings this set is insane.<br>
<br>
All three are great, and I would imagine you have read a few of them, but they are the three main sets that most Sci Fi authors say that got them into Sci Fi hard core.<br>
<br>
The Elric series, Moorcock did a great job with this set, and tied it into a few more sets of books.  This is one of my favorites of all time, it is a fun read.<br>
<br>
So after listing stiff that is at least 20 to 50 years old, let the flames begin... <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=233518">Sensei Shebaa The Transcendent</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
