The foundation series was awesome, and what Greg Bear and the others added into it, made it all the better. Though Foundation's End, I thought was kind of weak and pissed me off the way it wound up, but still pretty good.<br>
If you want to step out of the Sci-Fi genre and into Fantasy, read the Sword of Truth series from Terry Goodkind. It is an awesome weave of the psychological development of the characters as well as action. Magic is really kind of laid back in the books, but very much a part of them.  He makes some awesome comments about humanity in the series.<br>
Also, the Shannara series of books from Terry Brooks is an excellent story line, though the first several of which are written at what I feel was kind of an amateur level, having read the Heritage of Shannara first.<br>
His Knight of the Word series is actually tied into the Shannara series, though it's not actually made clear in any real way, but after reading them all, you'll get it.<br>
Oh, and don't let Millenium Man, the Robin Williams flick scare you off of the Foundation/robot series. That was based on the first short story of that whole series. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub114.ezboard.com/blegacyofsteel43089.showUserPublicProfile?gid=taelnayael>Taelnayael</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/10/03 12:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3790.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Books</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Robert Jordan needs to fucking tie up some ends. I havent read the last book yet and the book before that he cleared the taint, so maybe there is some hope.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
